  "body": "Latest master branch\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce:\r\n\r\nThis is not easy to reproduce. It happens when running many tests right after each other but not from the command line. A `curl` command similar to this one is being called repeatedly during TrueBlocks' tests: \r\n\r\n```\r\ncurl -X POST --data '{\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"method\":\"eth_getBalance\",\"params\":[\"0xa1e4380a3b1f749673e270229993ee55f35663b4\",\"0x1\"],\"id\":64}' -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" localhost:8545\r\n```\r\n\r\nBut when I call that curl command from the command line, it succeeds.\r\n\r\n#### Comments:\r\n\r\nTrueBlocks calls `eth_getBalance` around 1,000 times during its tests. Sometimes (10 out of 1,000?), `eth_getBalance` reports an ERROR in the log (copied below). The log points to [this line](https://github.com/ledgerwatch/turbo-geth/blob/master/cmd/rpcdaemon/commands/get_balance.go#L24) which dereferences the return from `acc.Balance.ToBig()` without first checking for error. Clearly, there needs to be a test for error at that line, but not sure why it works sometimes and not others.\r\n\r\nThe tests run very quickly one right after the other, so maybe that's related.\r\n\r\n`eth_getBalance` is the only RPC command that shows this type of error.\r\n\r\n```\r\nDEBUG[09-10|23:04:06.026] Served                                   conn=127.0.0.1:63323 t=1.322612ms   method=eth_getBalance                          reqid=1 params=\"[\\\"0xa1e4380a3b1f749673e270229993ee55f35663b4\\\",\\\"0x1\\\"]\"\r\nERROR[09-10|23:04:06.027] RPC method eth_getBalance crashed: runtime error: invalid memory address or nil pointer dereference\r\ngoroutine 111993 [running]:\r\ngithub.com/ledgerwatch/turbo-geth/rpc.(*callback).call.func1(0xc000517260, 0xe, 0xc000197d58)\r\n\tgithub.com/ledgerwatch/turbo-geth/rpc/service.go:200 +0xb5\r\npanic(0x4bb0520, 0x56c7910)\r\n\truntime/panic.go:967 +0x166\r\ngithub.com/ledgerwatch/turbo-geth/cmd/rpcdaemon/commands.(*APIImpl).GetBalance(0xc00007e960, 0x4ed1b80, 0xc0002a7040, 0xc3b2382cf5af7df2, 0xdf2d6592932bad73, 0xc5033343, 0xc0005172b8, 0x0, 0x0, 0x0, ...)\r\n\tgithub.com/ledgerwatch/turbo-geth/cmd/rpcdaemon/commands/get_balance.go:24 +0x1e8\r\nreflect.Value.call(0xc00021a600, 0xc0000a25c8, 0x13, 0x4d0342c, 0x4, 0xc00061a120, 0x4, 0x4, 0xc000061bf0, 0x404ee3c, ...)\r\n\treflect/value.go:460 +0x8ab\r\nreflect.Value.Call(0xc00021a600, 0xc0000a25c8, 0x13, 0xc00061a120, 0x4, 0x4, 0x2, 0x2, 0x0)\r\n\treflect/value.go:321 +0xb4\r\ngithub.com/ledgerwatch/turbo-geth/rpc.(*callback).call(0xc000098900, 0x4ed1b80, 0xc0002a7040, 0xc000517260, 0xe, 0xc000359e90, 0x2, 0x2, 0x0, 0x0, ...)\r\n\tgithub.com/ledgerwatch/turbo-geth/rpc/service.go:206 +0x2b7\r\ngithub.com/ledgerwatch/turbo-geth/rpc.(*handler).runMethod(0xc000137050, 0x4ed1b80, 0xc0002a7040, 0xc000338540, 0xc000098900, 0xc000359e90, 0x2, 0x2, 0x2)\r\n\tgithub.com/ledgerwatch/turbo-geth/rpc/handler.go:388 +0x8a\r\ngithub.com/ledgerwatch/turbo-geth/rpc.(*handler).handleCall(0xc000137050, 0xc000359e30, 0xc000338540, 0x203000)\r\n\tgithub.com/ledgerwatch/turbo-geth/rpc/handler.go:336 +0x298\r\ngithub.com/ledgerwatch/turbo-geth/rpc.(*handler).handleCallMsg(0xc000137050, 0xc000359e30, 0xc000338540, 0x4ebdf01)\r\n\tgithub.com/ledgerwatch/turbo-geth/rpc/handler.go:298 +0x1bd\r\ngithub.com/ledgerwatch/turbo-geth/rpc.(*handler).handleMsg.func1(0xc000359e30)\r\n\tgithub.com/ledgerwatch/turbo-geth/rpc/handler.go:139 +0x46\r\ngithub.com/ledgerwatch/turbo-geth/rpc.(*handler).startCallProc.func1(0xc000137050, 0xc000365660)\r\n\tgithub.com/ledgerwatch/turbo-geth/rpc/handler.go:226 +0xcd\r\ncreated by github.com/ledgerwatch/turbo-geth/rpc.(*handler).startCallProc\r\n\tgithub.com/ledgerwatch/turbo-geth/rpc/handler.go:222 +0x66\r\nWARN [09-10|23:04:06.027] Served                                   conn=127.0.0.1:63323 method=eth_getBalance                          reqid=1 t=1.269375ms   err=\"method handler crashed\"\r\n```\r\n",
